title: Understanding Categorical Data
text: Categorical data represents distinct categories or groups. It is often used to label or name different items or entities.

title: Examples of Categorical Data
text: Examples of categorical data include gender, colors, or types of animals. These are labels that do not have a numerical value and only discrete values.

title: Differentiating from Numerical Data
text: Unlike numerical data, categorical data cannot be measured or ordered numerically. It is used to describe characteristics or qualities.

title: Comparing Ordinal and Categorical Data
text: Ordinal data is also sorted into categories, but the order of the categories matter compared to categorical data where the categories can be in any order.
